INSERT INTO `cbJobs` VALUES (1,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3F1LL79STZQJV0LB4H','\nOur client is currently seeking a Data Scientistï¿½Job Title: Data ScientistJob Location : Austin,TXLocal candidates prefer\nï¿½ï¿½ ï¿½Job Description:The data scientist will partner with business teams across a variety of areas and applications.ï¿½\nHe/she will work with business partners to understand business objectives and scope analytical projects that deliver insights and results.ï¿½\nHe/she will work hands-on with large disparate datasets and analyze them leveraging state-of-the-art techniques and tools.ï¿½\nHe/ she will also work in a cross-functional manner with other consultants, analysts, statisticians, data engineers, and external vendors to deliver insights and solutions based on machine learning, statistical and econometric analyses.ï¿½\nï¿½Displaying strong business acumen and communication skills, the data scientist will communicate analytical results to business partner in various settings to help drive results.ï¿½\nOur business partners place great emphasis on our ability to translate statistical and mathematical results in way that tells a clear story and guides them in actionable decisions.ï¿½\n\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nScope analytics projects including identifying resources and assets needed, determining analysis approach, conducting analysis, and developing execution plansï¿½\n* Work independently or collaboratively throughout the complete analytics project lifecycle including data extraction/preparation, design and implementation of scalable machine learning analysis and solutions, and documentation of resultsï¿½\n* Refine, improve and take ownership of existing machine learning models, systems and implementations; Refine and improve data science workflow and processesï¿½\n* Partner with technical and non-technical resources across the business to leverage their support and integrate our efforts * Partner with infrastructure and platform teams to configure, tune tools, automate tasks and guide the evolution of internal big data ecosystem; serve as a bridge between data scientists and infrastructure/platform teams * Pro-actively analyze data to uncover insights that increase business value and impact * Support various business partners on a wide range of analytics projects from ad-hoc requests to large-scale cross-functional engagements * Approach analytical problems with an appropriate blend of statistical/mathematical rigor with practical business intuition.ï¿½\nï¿½* Hold a point-of-view on the strengths and limitations of statistical models and analyses in various business contexts and is able to evaluate and effectively communicate the uncertainty in the results * Approach analyses in multiple ways in order to evaluate approaches and compare results Bring a creative approach to quantitative analysis and problem solving and is able to comfortably think outside the traditional methodologies from the academic literature.ï¿½\nï¿½* MS/PhD in Machine Learning, Computer Science or other quantitative disciplines highly preferred * 2+ years of industry experience as a data scientist or machine learning engineerï¿½\n* Experience in financial services would be a plus but not necessarily a requirementï¿½\n* Strong understanding of how analytics supports a large organization including being able to successfully articulate the linkage between business objectives, analytical approaches & findings and business decisions,ï¿½\n* Excellent analytical skills with demonstrated ability to solve problemsï¿½\n* Mastery of Python plus SQL programming/data processing experience (knowledge of SAS and SAS macro programming would be a plus); knowledge or ability to learn Scala, R as necessary * Strong experience with Apache Spark and related ecosystem * Ability to work with large transactional databases across multiple platforms (Teradata, Oracle, HDFS, SAS)\nï¿½* Experience in visualizations and visualization frameworks such as d3 would be a plus * Good oral and written communicationï¿½\n* Strong interpersonal skills to successfully build long-term relationships with colleagues and business partners * A results-driven individual with a passion for data/analytics who can work collaboratively with others to solve business problems that drive business growth\n','Austin, TX'),(2,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3G1JG5WGLG2M4SJ7WG','\nKellyMitchell matches the best IT and business talent with premier organizations nationwide. Our clients, ranging from Fortune 500 corporations to rapidly growing high-tech companies, are exceptionally served by our 1500+ IT and business consultants. Our industry is growing rapidly, and now is a great time to launch your career with the KellyMitchell team.Position Title:ï¿½ï¿½ Data Scientistï¿½Position Summary: This candidate will do predictive modeling for new high-visibility projects, as a member of a collaborative and open team that prides themselves on innovation in a high performing, solution-oriented culture. The data scientist will explore information from multiple sources in order to gain maximum insight that can give the company a competitive advantage.ï¿½ ï¿½Performs data studies of new and diverse data sources.ï¿½ ï¿½Conducts statistical modeling and experiment design.ï¿½ ï¿½Discovers ï¿½storiesï¿½ told by the data and presents them to other scientists, software developers, business analysts and business managers.ï¿½ ï¿½Creates and validates predictive models and advanced algorithms.ï¿½ ï¿½Designs, modifies and builds new data processes.ï¿½\nRequired Skills/Experience:Strong knowledge of programming and pattern recognition.ï¿½ ï¿½Possesses a mastery of statistics, machine learning, algorithms, predictive modeling, and advanced mathematics.ï¿½ Use SQL (Structured Query Language) and other programming languages (R, C++, Perl) for statistical computing, graphics, and data mining.ï¿½ ï¿½Experience with RDBMS, columnar and NoSQL database technologies, Hadoopï¿½ ï¿½Possesses strong exploratory analysis skills and ability to think and research creatively.ï¿½ ï¿½Demonstrates excellent verbal and written communication skills as well as the ability to bridge the gap between data science and business management.ï¿½ ï¿½Data Analytics: Collaborate with business unit, IT, and data scientists across the enterprise to support descriptive and predictive analytics process.ï¿½ ï¿½Master\'s Degree in either/or Science (physics), Technology, Engineering and Mathematics (statistics) plus 7 years analytics and data science or Ph.D. in either/or Science (physics), Technology, Engineering and Mathematics (statistics) plus 3 years of analytics and data science.ï¿½ ï¿½Note that the term ï¿½data scienceï¿½ above includes both data mining and predictive modeling.ï¿½ ï¿½Applicants must have experience with Big Data and related tools such as Hadoop or Spark and statistics packages like ï¿½Rï¿½.\n\n','Colorado Springs, CO'),(3,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3H6PP6JJCJLJK8R12V','\nThis Data Scientist position is ideal for a software engineer that enjoys supporting legacy and new systems development and continuous improvement of mission centric information systems. Position will work with a mixed team of developers and government mission specialists. Flexibility and strong communications skills are essential to succeed in this environment. Work will support very large structured and unstructured datasets and require scripting toextract, transform, and load (ETL) data for analysis.This is an opportunity to work withspecialized mission area experts in data analysis. Ability to translate statistical and analytical requirements to programmers is essential.Position requires an active Top Secret clearance with SCI upgrade eligibility. Must be willing to undergo a CI poly. Personnel supporting this task shall: ï¿½ Interpret and analyze data using exploratory and statistical techniques; ï¿½ Develop, implement and utilize data systems and other strategies that optimize statistical efficiency and data quality; ï¿½ Develop innovations in data analysis techniques; ï¿½ Analyze and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets; ï¿½ Develop data modeling methods; ï¿½ Work with data scientists to coordinate multifaceted scientific research and analytic activities that provides scientific and technical consultation. Minimum Education And Experience\n Bachelor\'s Degree with 5+ years of related experience. Will consider additonal years of expeirence in lieu of degree.Required Skills And Education\nQualified candidates are required to have:Active Top Secret security clearance and SCI eligibility. Must be willing to undergo a CI poly. \nExperience working with intel data analysis both in the development of analytical tools and the use of the tools to produce mission focused reports. \n5+ years of information technology experience with an emphasis on computer or information science or applied mathematics is preferred \nAbility to create and use innovative link analysis tools \n2+ years of experience with Python, JAVA and R \n2+ years of experience with Hadoop \nMultiple industry recognized certifications in provisioning technologies such as Cloudera Certified Professional, SAS Certified Big Data Expert, Certified Specialist in Predictive Analytics (CSPA)\nAbout BAE Systems Intelligence & Security\n BAE Systems Intelligence & Security, based in McLean, Virginia, designs and delivers advanced defense, intelligence, and security solutions that support the important missions of our customers. Our pride and dedication shows in everything we do-from intelligence analysis, cyber operations and IT expertise to systems development, systems integration, and operations and maintenance services. Knowing that our work enables the U.S. military and government to recognize, manage and defeat threats inspires us to push ourselves and our technologies to new levels. That\'s BAE Systems. That\'s Inspired Work. Equal Opportunity Employer/Females/Minorities/Veterans/Disabled/Sexual Orientation/Gender Identity/Gender Expression. To see Inspired Work in action, visit www.baesystems.com and follow us on Facebook: www.facebook.com/baesystemsintel.\n','Washington, DC'),(4,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3H7JH74BYMW0V5WCYB','\nOur client, a telecommunications company in Andover, MA, is in need of a Data Scientist for a three-month contract-to-hire position. The Data Scientist will be driving Predictive Analytics and AI solutions, working in conjunction with an Analytics group comprised of a Team Lead, two Data Architects, and four offshore BI Analysts. The Data Scientist will be creating Analytics solutions from scratch ï¿½ the Data Environment isnï¿½t fully defined yet, so thereï¿½s great opportunity and freedom to work definition-to-deployment. Core responsibilities include defining the data state, pulling from internal data sources and building out the unstructured data pool, integration of monitoring tools, and supporting data automation operations. The Data Scientist will also be responsible for tool and platform assessment, selection, and deployment ï¿½ this is both a research and development role. Required Skills: 10+ yearsï¿½ overall Data Analytics experience 3+ yearsï¿½ experience at the Lead/Architect/Scientist level Must have worked on Operational Analytics solutions from the requirement phase through deployment, in a production environment, and be able to speak to this process  Experience in assessing a business environment, determining valuable data connections, and building unstructured data pools for manipulation Deep understanding of Predictive Analytics and AI tools on the market Experience leading tool assessment and selection is major plus  Excellent communication and collaboration skills Preferred Skills: Prior experience working with offshore analyst teams ','Andover, MA'),(5,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3K6MJ6P3P684LG81Q7','\nJob DescriptionPosition Overview/Description:The Visual Data Scientist & Data analyst positions discover and curate new and existing data sources to create solutions for the business. These key positions help bring data to life to solve business problems. At times, the problem is identified by a business unit, frequently wishing to optimize cost, revenue, or improve quality, and at times problems are formulated by the Data Scientists. Solutions are then envisioned that harness internal and external data and (in the case of the Visualization side) through advanced visualizations, provide the ability for users to answer their key questions.Responsibilities: Supports all enterprise units including Business Units and Skill Teams\nResponsible for creating new data visualizations, including: \nProblem formulation and design of solution\nHarvesting of data from multiple systems globally \nCollaborating with Analytics and IT teams to transforming the data for use in modeling and visualizations\nDesigning visual interface for users to interact with the data; building visualizations \nIdentify relationships in data to assist in providing insights\nEvaluation of data accuracy, completeness, timeliness, and stability to establish repeatable, sustainable processes to maintain \nData visualization team will train and deployment of the new tools\nBasic Qualifications:Bachelorï¿½s degree \n1+ years of experience with one or more of the following tools: Data Gathering skills/tools (e.g. SQL, Hadoop, Teradata, SAS, Business Objects, etc.) or Visualization skills/tools (e.g. QlikView, Tableau, WebFocus, etc.)\nPreferred Qualifications:Masterï¿½s degree with a strong background in data science \nStrong collaboration and communications skills\nStrong problem formulation and problem solving skills \nExperience communicating findings to make data analysis actionable and understandable by business partners\nAbility to take complex problems and break them down to create an implement an action plan\nStrong understanding of analysis and computational complexity and ability to programmatically solve problems\nStrong capabilities at designing visual interface for data interaction\n The distance between imagination and ï¿½ creation. It can be measured in years of innovation, or in moments of brilliance. When you join the Ford team discover all the benefits, rewards and development opportunities youï¿½d expect from a diverse global leader. Youï¿½ll become part of a team that is already leading the way, with ingenious solutions and attainable products ï¿½ and it is always to go further.Candidates for positions with Ford Motor Company must be legally authorized to work in the United States on a permanent basis. Verification of employment eligibility will be required at the time of hire. Visa sponsorship is not available for this position. Ford Motor Company is an equal opportunity employer committed to a culturally diverse workforce. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, religion, color, age, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability status or protected veteran status.','Washington DC, DC'),(6,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3L1D663QY06SZGP9HP','\nRef ID: 03720-0010076909Classification: Business AnalystCompensation: DOEMy client is looking for a Data Scientist in Horsham, PA. If interested in the role, email me directly at [Click Here to Email Your Resumï¿½] <U+0095> Evaluate data project requirements and determine the best data solution, strategy and approach. <U+0095> Establish data migration and integration plans. <U+0095> Manage internal and external client expectations on all project requirements and deliverables with frequent communication, documentation and regular scope verification. <U+0095> Provide full and accurate project communication with the internal and external clients and vendors <U+0095> Proactively identify changes in work scope and ensure appropriate planning measures are taken with internal and external clients to reassess and amend the scope of work requirement, budget, and timeline <U+0095> Analyze and resolve issues that have the potential to jeopardize the ability to meet agreed upon deliverables <U+0095> Manage a project repository including project planning documents, access privileges, a project calendar, an issues list, a change request list, shared documents, links, and a key contacts list. <U+0095> Experienced in working with various data vendors and project consultants. <U+0095> Experience using Salesforce enterprise 1 (SASS) If interested in the Data Scientist role, email me directly at [Click Here to Email Your Resumï¿½]\n','Horsham, PA'),(7,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3L1K96DTG4V71RT5Z0','\n USA TODAY NETWORKï¿½is one of the top 20 digital companies in the country, sharing the list with Google, Facebook, and Amazon. And we have over 100 million unique visitors a month, which is more than Buzzfeed, Yahoo News, and Huffington Post. We have a loyal following based on a combination of trusted, fact-checked journalism, paired with a deep commitment to helping our local communities, and constantly pushing our content delivery to be first-of-its-kind in the tech-space. Explore the opportunity as a Data Scientist with Gannett.  ï¿½  B2B Analytics & Data Strategy   Data Scientist   Do you want to use data to transform a media organization? Gannett is seeking a Data Scientist with a strong blend of analytical and technical skills to develop data-driven insights that will guide strategies and decisions within Gannettï¿½s B2B businesses, which include over 80 community newspapers and websites.   You will help build a holistic understanding of our customers by integrating both structured and unstructured data ranging from ad logs to content. You understand the technicalities of data but can also explain your findings in laymanï¿½s terms. You understand that business questions are often not well-defined but will proactively help stakeholders get to a data solution. You have an inquisitive mind and sound judgement when it comes to distinguishing signal from noise.   You can talk to data but also get along well with people.   The ideal candidate:    Has a passion for understanding data, with strong knowledge in at least one of the following: machine learning, data mining, statistical modeling, data visualization.     Is able to generate actionable insights by quickly formulating and testing hypotheses in large datasets using techniques like regression, ensembling, classification etc.     Is solution oriented, with an ability to collaborate cross functionally and with regional and national sales and marketing teams to identify and address their pain points.     Can work autonomously and deliver timely results in a highly-organized manner.     Proactively innovates in both presentation and approach to make end products engaging and user-friendly.    Responsibilities    Maintain and enhance current models and tools for Sales and Marketing teams.     Evaluate, understand and process large data sets from multiple internal and 3rd party data sources.     Consult with regional and nationwide teams to understand business needs.     Utilize analytics to develop new insights and identify new Sales and Marketing opportunities.     Measure, test and learn to deliver increasingly valuable, repeatable and scalable analytic solutions.    Qualifications    BA/BS in a quantitative field (Computer Science, Economics, Math, Statistics, or Engineering) degree is required.     MA/PhD with emphasis on data mining, or Bachelors plus 3-5 years of relevant experience preferred.     Excellent analytical, quantitative and statistical problem solving skills.     Excellent oral and written communication skills.     Experience using tools such as Python, R, and/or SAS. Extensive experience with SQL a plus.     Familiarity with Hadoop, Hive, Spark and AWS a plus.    We are a drug free, EEO employer committed to a diverse workforce. We will consider all qualified candidates regardless of race, color, national origin, sex, age, marital status, personal appearance, sexual orientation, family responsibilities, disability, education, political affiliation or veteran status. #Technology #LI-MH1ï¿½ï¿½\n','McLean, VA'),(8,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3L7S66HT4SK7QT235Y','\nKey Responsibilities:Own evolution of data science roadmap and manage major initiatives and milestones around modeling for various areas such as discovery, marketing and teaching & learning. This will involve cross functional team collaboration (involving remote teams), resource allocation, development, and production model deployment.\nOwn our data science modeling infrastructure and defines model building and hand-over process with Data engineering team and other engineering stakeholders.\nManage 5+ team leads/members in our San Francisco office. Set goals for each team member based on company initiatives and manage and mentor them to effectively deliver on those goals through technical leadership, personal coaching, and collaboration. Put metrics in place to measure quality and quantity of contributions.\nRecruit, hire, and retain a credible team that meets delivery commitments while being responsive to product and business teams.\nContinue to challenge status quo in terms of development processes and best engineering practices. Promote healthy debates around new tools and processes and champion changes that have positive impact.\nBuild a team culture that values quality, robustness, and scalability of our data science approach while fostering initiatives and innovation.\nGrow and mentor leaders within the engineering organization.\nFoster fun, friendly, and collaborative team environment for retention and recruiting.\nWork with internal and external recruiters to attract high quality candidates. Oversee the hiring process to fill open positions while strengthening the team diversity and capacity. \nEngage and participate in external data science meetups and events to promote our engineering brand as a great place to work. Give tech talks or organize data scientist panels.\nPublish in conferences, writing data blogs and so on to make Data Science work at our more visible.\nQualifications:PhD or equivalent experience in computer science or a quantitative field. PhD preferred\n10+ years of experience in industry experience, preferably in high traffic consumer internet services\n5+ years proven leadership experience, hiring, coaching, developing and engaging data scientists or engineers\nStrong understanding of statistics, machine learning and natural language processing\nFamiliarity with coding and engineering implementation\nSthree US is acting as an Employment Agency in relation to this vacancy.\n','San Francisco, CA'),(9,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3N28H6CTMLX2DFQTF8','\nThis position is open as of 10/8/2017.Data Scientist | Awarded Startup of the Year!!If you are a Data Scientist with machine learning experience, please read on!Situated mere minutes from one of Orange County\'s most picturesque ocean front views is a stimulating opportunity for Data Scientists who want to solve complex problems and have some fun doing it. We are building a platform that will revolutionize the construction industry by utilizing cloud-based technology that is scalable and easy to use. We provide a SaaS platform that links to different shared devices that streamlines the building process, linking many shared devices for more effective planning as well as efficiency! As an experienced Data Scientist, you will collaborate with our team about how to build a more comprehensive software. You will build machine learning algorithms, using various data mining techniques and working with cloud-based software to do it. We want to transform every building, whether it is new or old, into a smart building and we are utilizing IoT, Machine Learning and Cloud technology to do so!What You Need for this Position- Bachelor\'s Degree (Master\'s or PhD, even better!) At Least 3 Years of experience and knowledge of:- Machine Learning- Python- Data MiningNice to Have: - IoT- Cloud Tech (AWS ideally)What\'s In It for You- $120-175k DOE- Vacation/PTO- Medical- Dental- Vision- 401(k)- Telecommute Days - Equity- Company Sponsored Events- Innovative Tech- Open Floor Plan - Catered Lunches- Relaxed DressSo, if you are a Data Scientist with IoT experience, please apply today!Required SkillsMachine Learning, Python, Data MiningIf you are a good fit for the Data Scientist | Awarded Startup of the Year!! position, and have a background that includes:Machine Learning, Python, Data Mining and you are interested in working the following job types:Information Technology, Engineering, Professional ServicesWithin the following industries:ConstructionOur privacy policy: Your resume and information will be kept completely confidential.Looking forward to receiving your resume through our website and going over the job in more detail with you!CyberCoders, Inc is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, disability, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law.Your Right to Work ï¿½ In compliance with federal law, all persons hired will be required to verify identity and eligibility to work in the United States and to complete the required employment eligibility verification document form upon hire.\n','San Clemente, CA'),(10,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3Q7766SC6K3RK1FV2W','\nLaSalle Network is currently partnering with a fast growing startup to identify a mid-level Data Scientist to join their team. Our client focuses on the consumer shopping market and this individual will work on a team of 3 other Data Science professionals to help provide analytical solutions that help their clients get rich insights. This is a full time, salaried position with benefits and this is also an onsite position in Chicago (no relocation assistance provided).Data Scientist Responsibilities:Create R/Python programming modules for custom insights. Leverage statistical analysis to understand what is \"acceptable\" versus \"outliers\"\nContribute to Data Exploration needed to enhance the cleanliness and effectiveness data sources\nPresent insights to clients through data visualization\nPerform analyses that demonstrate the data\'s value and build algorithms that elevate the platform\nData Scientist Requirements: Minimum of 2 years\' experience in a data analysis, business intelligence, or data science position (we can count internships or school research as experience).\nProficient programming skills in at least 2 of the following (SQL, python, R, or SAS).\nFamiliarity with the works of Spark, AWS S3\nFamiliarity with some sort of data visualization tool\nStrong analytical and communications skills, ability to work within a team, and ability to keep on schedule in fast paced development environment\nIf you are interested in this Data Scientist position and meet the requirements, please apply today!Thank You,Jim Halpin Team Lead, Technology Services LaSalle NetworkKeywords and Related Terms: data science, Python, R, SAS, SQL, business intelligence, data analytics, consumer insights.The LaSalle Network is an Equal Opportunity Employer, m/f/d/v.LaSalle Network is the leading provider of professional staffing and recruiting services. LaSalle has worked with more than 10,000 companies, ranging from Fortune 500s to start ups. With units specializing in administrative, accounting and finance, marketing, executive search, technology, sales, supply chain, healthcare revenue cycle, call center, and human resources, LaSalle serves companies of all sizes and across all industries.\n','Chicago, IL'),(11,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3R2M65ZF4ZFYJ5SDVQ','\nJobID: 15790Data Scientistï¿½Skills: Data mining, statistics, operations research, Master degree in related field, 3+ yearï¿½s professional experiencePay:ï¿½$70,000 - $80,000 based on experienceLocation: Kennesaw, GA Our client is seeking highly talented Data Scientists to join a growing company in their new Alpharetta HQ. This global company is significantly expanding their Metro Atlanta team as to keep up with their ever growing client base.ï¿½Requirements:Masterï¿½s degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Engineering or related field 3+ years of relevant experience Strong knowledge and understanding in at least one of following data mining, machine learning, statistics, operations research, econometrics and/or information retrieval In depth knowledge in extracting, preparing, and modeling data; command-line scripting, data structures, and algorithms; and working in a Linux environment Proficiency in analysis packages such as R, SAS, Matlab Proficiency in programming languages such as Ruby, Scala, Python or Java\nResponsibilities:Retrieve & process a rich data variety from sources such as social media, news, internal/external documents, emails, financial, and operational data Use statistical and mathematical methods, data mining and econometrics to analyze and model structured data and implement algorithms to support analysis. Use methods such as documentï¿½clustering, topic analysis, named entity recognition, document classification, and sentiment analysis to perform statistical natural language processing\n Utilize technologies and tools to deliver insights, such as R, SAS, Python, Spark, Hadoop, Qlikview, and Tableau Translate business analytics problems into technical approaches that yield actionable recommendations Perform exploratory data analysis to uncover interesting trends and relationships\nBenefits: (Probably some of the best benefits out there)Company paid medical coverage along with funded HSA Long and short term disability Company 401Kï¿½ PTO, fixed holiday and floating days Great company culture ï¿½ Casual dress\n*CB\n','Kennesaw, GA'),(12,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3V2KT7611KRLVVYZN9','\nThe Data Scientist will perform activities to support technical data and information analysis and reporting across key technical governance applications and platforms, collaborate with key business stakeholders to optimize and streamline reporting and metrics, and implement solutions to create better business value. This position will work under the guidance and direction of the Analytics and Insights Director, and will actively collaborate with extended team members from Data Intelligence team.Function Related Activities/Key ResponsibilitiesWork on the process of translating technical objectives into defined problems that can be solved by applying data science\nHelp to design algorithms to address current technical problems\nWork closely with data analysts in the team to apply advanced analytics, modelling and simulation to replicate and anticipate issues.\nUncover new technical problems that need to be solved and support better decision\nCommunicate data analysis and insights using rich visualization tools (Tableau/MicroStrategy) and leverage data to present compelling cases to optimize solutions\nPerform exploratory data analysis, generate and test working hypothesis, and uncover important trends and relationships\nProvide expertise on mathematical concepts and inspire adoption of advanced analytics\nEducation Requirements:ï¿½  Masterï¿½s Degree in applied statistics, applied math, or related quantitative disciplineRelated Work Experience:ï¿½  0-2 years of relevant experienceExperience with relational databases, information and insights\nExperience with modelling software, data mining techniques and methodologies\nExperience with visualization software (Tableau, MicroStrategy)\nExperience leveraging cloud platforms and developing in SQL\nSuperior critical thinking, analytical and problem-solving skills.\nPassionate, creative and forward thinking individual\nLeadership Behaviors:ï¿½Drive Innovation:ï¿½ Generate new or unique solutions and embrace new ideas that help sustain our business (encompassing everything from continuous improvement to new product and package innovation)\nCollaborate with System and Stakeholders:ï¿½ Develop and leverage relationships with stakeholders to appropriately stretch and impact the System (Company and Bottler)\nAct Like an Owner:ï¿½ Deliver results, creating value for our brands, our System, our customers and key stakeholders\nInspire Others:ï¿½ Inspire people to deliver our mission and 2020 Vision, demonstrate passion for the business and give people a reason to believe anything is possible\nDevelop Self and Others:ï¿½ Develop self and support othersï¿½ development to achieve full potential\nGrowth Behaviors:Growth Mindset:ï¿½ Demonstrates Curiosity.ï¿½ Welcomes failure as a learning opportunity.\nSmart Risk:ï¿½ Makes bold decisions/recommendations\nExternally Focused:ï¿½ Understands the upstream and downstream implications of his/her work.ï¿½ Tracks and shares external trends, best practices, or ideas.\nPerformance Driven & Accountable:ï¿½ Has high performance standards.ï¿½ Outperforms her/his peers.\nFast/Agile:ï¿½ Removes barriers to move faster.ï¿½ Experiments and adapts.ï¿½ Thrives under pressure and fast pace.\nEmpowered:ï¿½ Brings solutions instead of problems.ï¿½ Challenges the status quo.ï¿½ Has the courage to take an unpopular stance.\nFunctional Skills: ï¿½Capture Info/Assess/Make Recommendation. Capture information, assess it and make recommendations to Company management (e.g., senior technical management) or give the KO system information about emerging business opportunities, technology capabilities or scientific breakthroughs to offer solutions to technical problems and/or affect the Company\'s strategic direction.\nGather/Org Info to Support Senior Mgmt. Decision. Gather and organize information to support senior management\'s decision-making during a crisis situation.\nPerformance Data Audit to Ensure Accuracy. Perform data audit in order to ensure accuracy of data and analytical processes. This may include database queries, statistical process control or correlation study.\nQuery Technical Governance Systems/Compile Reports. Query Technical Governance Systems and compile reports in response to ad hoc management requests or arrange for Global IT to run more complex queries.\nReview Data for Completeness/Consistency. Review data for completeness and consistency in formula and/or regulatory databases, tracking systems, supplier documentation, etc.\nReport/Analyze/Interpret Data. Report, analyze or interpret technical governance data in order to communicate information on the quality of products and packages in manufacturing or the marketplace.\nSearch External Databases. Search external and/or internal computerized databases in response to inquiries from scientists or to provide information to management or the field.\nApply Basic Statistical Tests/Methods. Apply basic statistical tests and methods to data in order to support Company decision-making by ensuring validity and statistical relevance.\nWork on the process of translating technical objectives into defined problems can be solved by applying data science\nHelp to design algorithms to address current technical problems\nWork closely with data analytics in the team to apply advanced analytics, modelling and simulation to replicate and anticipate issues\n\nHonesty and integrity have always been cornerstone values of The Coca-Cola Company. Our passion for people of integrity mirrors our spirited drive for total quality in our brands. These and other elements allow the company to sustain strategic practices and drive business performance. The Personnel Integrity Assurance Program is another step toward making The Coca-Cola Company the premier workplace. This process includes a pre-employment background investigation that applies to all applicants, employees, and contractors of the company. The scope of this inquiry may cover su