ience. \n 2+ years of experience in data analytics \n Excellent understanding of machine learning techniques and algorithms, such as k-NN, Naive Bayes, SVM, Decision Forests, etc. \n Experience with common data science toolkits, such as R, NumPy, Spark, Excellence in at least one of these is highly desirable \n Experience with data visualization tools, such as Tableau, etc \n Proficiency in using query languages such as SQL or equivalent \n Experience with NoSQL databases, such as MongoDB or equivalent \n Good applied statistics skills, such as distributions, statistical testing, regression, Bayesian, Markov chains, etc. \n Good scripting and programming skills in Python or equivalent \n Data-oriented personality \n We are proud to offer employees a benefit package designed to enhance your well-being and reward job performance. Some of these benefits include comprehensive healthcare coverage, paid holidays, paid vacation time, 401(K), vehicle lease/purchase programs.  Welcome to an open lane of possibility. Apply today. \n Applicants will be considered for all positions regardless of race, gender, military status, disability, or any other status protected by law. *Candidates for this position must be legally authorized to work in the United States.\n','San Jose, CA'),(28,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3H4VL6BHMCYWZ461WT','\nCALIBRE is looking for an experienced data analyst professional to join our team to support a large Army analytics and support effort. We are seeking a person that enjoys finding new sources for data-driven innovation; bringing structure and meaning to that data; joining with existing large data sets; dealing with imperfections in the data; and producing quantitative statistical analyses in creative, intelligent visual charts. Yes, we are seeking a data scientist.  The ideal candidate will work with our team to explore new ways to analyze data using statistical methods, machine learning and predictive models with the latest software. Candidat