ating interpretable visualizations\nSkills \nThe ideal candidate is someone with a desire for continual learning and strong problem-solving, analytic and interpersonal skills. You might be a great fit for our team if any of the following describe you: \n- Completed a degree program in the fields of mathematics, statistics, computer science, computational sciences, or a passion for rigorous analysis of data\n- Tenacity, integrity, persistence, and willingness to learn\n- Ability to solve complex problems\n- Use critical thinking and reasoning to make analytic determinations\n- Works effectively in a collaborative environment\n- Strong communications skills to both technical and non-technical audiencesï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ \n- The desire to serve over 300 million fellow Americans and make a difference in world events\n\n\n','Fort Meade, MD'),(96,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/JJ540270F4MWDCKD3MG','\n\nCyber Security Data Scientist / Data Analyst supporting the Department of Stateï¿½s Cyber Threat Analysis Division\nPart of growing team of data analysts working with volumes of collected cyber security data\nWork closely with cyber threat intelligence analysts, threat actor analysts, and malware specialists to analyze cyber threat data and deliver actionable cyber threat intelligence products\nAssist with data reviews, data validations, quality control, and data cleaning\nHelp develop and evolve ETL processes, develop data models, and create data processing pipelines to analyze disparate multi-source data\nDevelop and apply computational algorithms and statistical methods that find patterns and relationships in cyber threat intelligence data sets\nOpportunities to provide internal and external briefings to cyber security professionals of all technical levels on matters pertaining to data analytics and machine learningï¿½\nï¿½\n','Arlington, VA'),(97,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3F6FB63N04J26K9H7V','\nWe\'re changing the way health care works for the better. Tha