ssment, data management and data visualization as required. Under limited supervision, reviews and continuously executes the global post market surveillance process. Extracts monthly post market quality data and maintains compliant records. Follows procedures to investigate and analyze complaint trending and field data to determine significant issues and leads investigations to determine the causes of those issues from a post market surveillance standpoint. Monitors changes in post market quality signals and documents appropriately. Determines and implements solutions to monitoring customer and product quality issues through the application of statistical software and data analysis. Provides creative, thorough and practical data driven solutions to wide ranges of difficult problems. Remains informed of new or revised regulations and/or guidelines, and assesses impact on company post market surveillance processes. Creates presentations summarizing major product quality issues and complaint trends. Assists with verification and validation activities of post market surveillance reports and scripts. \nSupports quality engineering, customer quality and other groups on ad-hoc data analysis, data mining, data queries in support of CAPA and other product market quality related requests. Completes projects/other duties as assigned. Provides support during external and internal audits of the customer quality process. Qualifications A minimum of a Bachelor of Science degree in a technical field (for example, Mathematics, Statistics, Electrical Engineer, Mechanical Engineering, Computer Engineering, Industrial Engineering, Chemical Engineering, Chemistry, Biology, Public Health etc.) or a related field is required with 4-6 years of experience. Minimum of 2 years\' experience with a Master\'s Degree in a technical field or 0-1 years with a PhD in a technical field described above. Strong quantitative and critical thinking skills are required. An understanding of basic statistica