 to their causes and corrective actions to prevent recurrence.ï¿½\nIdentifies, plans, and implements quality and productivity initiatives associated to cleaning validation activities based on business needs and priorities.\nAssures the accuracy and correctness of documentation used to support cleaning validation activities.\n\n\nValidation Scientist-Cleaning\n\n','Devens, MA'),(137,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/JHR5W25X86W4854F8SQ','\nWe are looking for an exceptional Data Scientist to join our analytics team. Our team is responsible for providing analytical support related to improving our customers\' experience and products performance, identify key trends, and telling stories with data.ï¿½ Our team works cross-functionally with program, product and engineering teams. The primary focus of the data scientist will be to apply data mining techniques, doing statistical analysis, and building high quality presentations for our senior leadership team. You will help to discover information hidden in large data sets and define and build new sets of KPI to measure our products\' performance.ï¿½\nThe ideal candidate will be passionate about data-driven decision making and able to do analysis on large unstructured data sets and quickly grasp new technologies.ï¿½Responsibilities:Enhancing data collection procedures to include information that is relevant for building analytic systems\nProcessing, cleansing, and verifying the integrity of data used for analysis\nPerforming ad-hoc analysis and presenting results in a clear manner\nLead and coordinate meetings with key project stakeholders\n Collaborate with leadership team to identify, define and measure KPIs needed to drive improvement in customer experience\nDevelop reporting requirements and specifications with business and development teams.\nDesign, build and maintain dashboards that will be used by other teams and presented to Executives during weekly meetings, enabling stakeholders to make effective decisions\nConduct ad hoc data analysis and data quality investigations\nAnalyze granular data for segment and trend analysis\nData reconciliation and QA between different data feedsï¿½\nUse a variety of tools to analyze system performance and user behavior\nMonitor data trend and quality\n','Philadelphia, PA'),(138,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3H04L6LNDNDSHMVPVF','\n*Please no C2C applications*Lead Data Scientist (Bangkok) - FULL RELOCATION AND VISA SPONSORSHIP AVAILABLE Requirements:Do you have what it takes? * Excited and able to relocate to Bangkok, Thailand  * Leadership skills and experience in leading data science projects and or teams * At least 5 years working as a statistician / analyst / data scientist * An earned stripes in coding, in data handling, in statistics and in machine learning  * A good balance between theory and practice and a strong desire to learn and keep up with the latest technologies (a master degree in a quantitative field is a must; PhD is even better) * Battle-tested team leading skills * A good knowledge of what\'s \"Under the hood\" of statistical methods * Coding, coding, coding (R, Python, C#, Java, C++, Scala, ï¿½) * Some extra points on: SQL, NLP, business acumen, blog writing, good sense of humourCompany: Our client is the largest and fastest growing online hotel booking platform in Asia. With world class talent from over 65 countries, the atmosphere of a start-up and the muscle of a $bn business, this company is an incredible technical creative melting pot.Role:Technology is not just what they do - it\'s at the heart of who they are. Our client puts cutting-edge technology in your hands so you can help them change the way people run their lives. They are a high-growth company and maintaining this growth requires an incredible amount of data, a superior IT infrastructure, and world class talent to bring it all together.As a Senior Data Scientist you will be in involved in helping maintain our client\'s growth working with an incredible amount of data and leveraging the firm\'s superior IT infrastructure.Responsibilities:Leading from the front you will help my client: * Crack their business problems and come up with deployable machine learning models * Interface with business to make sure they are asking the right questions * Sift through their data and find them some gems  * Be a world-class hands-on deploy masterOur client offers: * Competitive annual salary * Medical coverage * Discounted hotel accommodation; anywhere in the world * Exposure to travel industry * Career advancement opportunities * Work environment: multinational * Dress code: smart casualWe welcome both local and international applications for this role. Full visa sponsorship and relocation assistance available for eligible candidates. If you are a Lead Data Scientist and this role appeals to you we want to hear from you straight away. Send us your CV now.\n','Washington, DC'),(139,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3H3KH71R1XFTN8YXVG','\nCardnoï¿½ ChemRisk, a scientific consulting company, provides state-of-the-art toxicology, industrial hygiene, epidemiology, and risk assessment services to organizations that confront public health, occupational health, and environmental challenges.\nOur team members have a long-standing reputation for thorough scientific analysis and for sharing results in the peer-reviewed scientific literature. Many of the over 500 papers that we have published present novel methodologies or address emerging advances\nin the health sciences, and have been frequently referenced in regulatory decision-making. Our mission is to provide creative and scientifically rigorous approaches to answering questions about the human health hazards posed by chemical, biological, pharmaceutical,\nand radiological agents.\nWe are currently seeking Senior Health Scientists (Senior Managing/Principal Scientists) to join our\nComputational Human Health Risk Assessment practice. We are particularly interested in consulting or subject matter experts with a successful record of business development in one or more of our computational sciences practice areas including environmental\nscience, computational toxicology and quantitative risk assessment. These positions offer a stimulating and challenging work environment and significant opportunities for professional growth.\nSuccessful applicants will have a multi-disciplinary background consisting of environmental, toxicological or human health risk assessment computational experience including business development and project experience in one or more of our practice areas including:Environmental Science: Air dispersion modeling, emissions permitting, environmental fate and transport analysis, chemical and particulate transport assessments, meteorological modeling/prognostic charting, groundwater transport analysis, indoor air quality\nmodeling, soil vapor emissions analysis, vapor intrusion analysis, product stewardship, and product life cycle assessmentToxicology: Computational pharmacology, food or drug compliance testing / toxicity testing, dose-response assessment, pharmacokinetic modeling, human clinical trial design, high-throughput drug screening, and quantitative structureï¿½activity relationship\nmodelingHuman Health Risk Assessment: Quantitative exposure modeling, industrial hygiene modeling, biostatistics, probabilistic analysis, database design and management\nSpecific activities and responsibilities for this position include:\n> Serve as a senior computational human health risk scientist in the firm responsible for securing and managing the execution of computational human health risk projects\n> Work with our corporate business development team to lead client development activities within the computational risk assessment practice area\n> Plan and attend meetings with prospective clients, identify business opportunities, and prepare proposals for projects with significant computational components\n> Publish and present study findings in the peer reviewed literature and at scientific conferences\n> Evaluate current literature and regulatory developments involving computational risk assessment\n> Provide strategic consulting and, if appropriate, testimony as an expert witness in litigation\n> Work with, manage, and mentor multi-disciplinary staff of health scientists including engineers, toxicologists, industrial hygienists, epidemiologists, environmental scientists and public health professionals\n> Some travel expected','San Francisco, CA'),(140,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/J3H62J5VN05FXY3MD7S','\nThis position is open as of 10/8/2017.Junior Healthcare Data Scientist - NLP, InformaticsWe are based just west of Boston, MA. We are a leader in Health Informatics that\'s improving drug related side effects and patient outcomes. We are looking for a Healthcare Data Scientist that wants to have direct impact on a team. If you have NLP experience and/or your have your graduate degree or PhD in Natural Language Processing, Data Science, Linguistics or a similar field , please read on!What You Will Be Doing- Collaborating with data architects, engineers, data scientists and analytics to work as a cohesive team to bring cognitive solutions to our Clients- Construct clustering and train classifiers for natural language processing of unstructured data- 75% customer facing and 25% projects related to query development using Python- Proactively seeking out and supporting new customer applications- Some troubleshooting during client presentations and giving feedback to our engineers on how to integrate their components.- 25% nationwide travel to client sites to give demos and trainingWhat You Need for this Position-2+ years of experience in programming with data analysis software, including Python or R in a professional work environment or during your research studies-2+ years of experience with analyzing large data sets for analytics-Understand the fundamentals of Natural Language Processing and articulate unstructured text analytic solutions in Client Deliverables-Experience with processing unstructured data and text with text manipulation libraries-Experience with applying machine learning at scale using recommender systems, NLP, or time series prediction-Domain knowledge-Ability to develop statistical tests to make data-driven recommendations and decisions-Excellent presentation and communication skills-Bachelors degree or higher in Linguistics, Machine Learning, Data Science, Life Sciences or a similar related fieldWhat\'s In It for You-We\'re dramatically impacting healthcare and helping industry leaders cure diabetes and other diseases -Competitive Salary Package including bonuses -Medical, Dental, Vision Benefits effective on your first day-401K plus matching-Vacation, holiday time and much more!So, if you have strong query experience and NLP experience, then please apply today!Required SkillsNatural Language Processing, Text Mining, Database Queries, Post Sales, Configuring Products with Clients, Face To Face Presentations, Scripting, Life Sciences, Clinical Experience, Domain KnowledgeIf you are a good fit for the Jr Application Scientist - NLP, Informatics position, and have a background that includes:Natural Language Processing, Text Mining, Database Queries, Post Sales, Configuring Products with Clients, Face To Face Presentations, Scripting, Life Sciences, Clinical Experience, Domain Knowledge and you are interested in working the following job types:Information Technology, Engineering, Professional ServicesWithin the following industries:Computer SoftwareOur privacy policy: Your resume and information will be kept completely confidential.Looking forward to receiving your resume through our website and going over the job in more detail with you!CyberCoders, Inc is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, disability, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law.Your Right to Work ï¿½ In compliance with federal law, all persons hired will be required to verify identity and eligibility to work in the United States and to complete the required employment eligibility verification document form upon hire.\n','Waltham, MA'),(141,'http://www.careerbuilder.com/job/JHT0SQ67TP8VGD2PLNC','\nData Scientist \nï¿½\nEXL (NASDAQ:EXLS) is a leading operations management and analytics company that helps businesses enhance growth and profitability in the face of relentless competition and continuous disruption. Headquartered in New York, New York, EXL has offices in United States, Europe, Asia, Latin America, Australia and South Africa.\n\nEXL Analytics provides data-driven, action-oriented solutions to business problems through statistical data mining and cutting edge analytics techniques. Leveraging proprietary methodology and best-of-breed technology, EXL Analytics takes an industry-specific approach to transform our clientsï¿½ decision making and embed analytics more deeply into their business processes. EXL Analytics serves clients across industries including healthcare, banking, insurance, retail and logistics.\n\nPlease visit www.exlservice.com for more information about EXL Analytics.\n\nJob Summary: \nEXL Analytics\nis developing advanced analytics solutions for some of the most exciting business\nproblems leveraging AI, NLP, Computer Vision and Speech.ï¿½ If you want to push the existing AI knowledge\nboundaries then we have an excellent opportunity for you. We are looking for Data\nScientists who can develop state of the art, scalable, and self-learning systems\nfor enterprises.ï¿½ Major responsibility will be to develop advanced\nanalytics solutions focusing on machine learning and deep learning capabilities.\n','Jersey City, NJ');
