gers. In close collaboration with Princeton\'s Office of Human Resources (HR) and Office of Information Technology (OIT), the incumbent ensures that DOF requirements are fully represented throughout the University\'s systems.ResponsibilitiesThe specific responsibilities of the Associate Dean for Data Analysis and Operations include:Communicating data analyses and reports to the Dean, DOF senior staff, University officers, and departmentsProactively identifying data trends, data quality issues and recommendations for improvementCurating DOF data, ensuring its integrity, security, accessibility and appropriate \"shelf life\"Participating in the development of policies related to data management and securityCollaborating with senior leadership and OIT to develop and maintain accurate, meaningful dashboards using key metrics and benchmarksRecommending and implementing an overall data management and web application strategyDocumenting and revising workflows and data flows to improve the efficiency of key business processesProviding functional input to HR and OIT in support of the systems used by DOFInsuring the accuracy and timeliness of revisions to and communications of DOF policies and proceduresQualificationsMaster\'s degree or higherFive or more years of experience working with quantitative data in a university or other academic context.Advanced knowledge of data warehouse environments.Strong background in the principles of research methods and data analysis.Ability to perform analyses on complex and disparate data sets.Experience in developing and using reporting and analysis tools to present data to a variety of audiences.Strong communication skillsProject and general management experience.Fluency with PeopleSoft or similar enterprise systems, as well as data reporting tools such as Tableau and IBM Cognos.Well developed Excel and Access skills; fluency with statistical software packages (SPSS, Stata, or R); experience with document management applications and systems such as OnBase.Ability to analyze user requirements, procedures and problems to automate or improve existing processesPlease submit a cover letter as well as a resume.The final candidate will be required to complete a background check successfully.Princeton University is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law. EEO IS THE LAWSalary GradeADM, 080Standard Weekly Hours36.25Eligible for OvertimeNoBenefits EligibleYesEssential Services Personnel (see policy for detail)NoPhysical Capacity Exam RequiredNoConnect With Us!Join our Talent Network to receive updates about working at Princeton.Princeton University requires all candidates to complete a background check successfully prior to the start of employment. The type and extent of background checks may vary depending on job requirements and/or functions.If you have questions or comments regarding the iCIMS Privacy Policy or iCIMS FAQs, please contact accounts@icims.com.Go to our careers site.Apply HerePI97733238					\n\n				\n\n			\n\n		','\n\n					Princeton, NJ 08544					\n\n				','Associate Dean for Data Analysis & Operations\r'),(4,'https://datajobs.com/Disney-Parks-Resorts/Decision-Science-Technical-Manager-Job~10489','\n\n			\n\n				\n\n					Job Description\n\n				\n\n			\n\n			\n\n				\n\n					Create innovative scientific models and data-driven decision support toolsï¿½as a member of our Decision Science team. Not sure where you fit in? We hail from many disciplines, including: Operations Research, Machine Learning, Statistics, Econometrics, Industrial Engineering, and Applied Mathematics. If your expertise lies in data mining, analytical consultation and science modeling, this could be the perfect role for you.Your Role:Achieve