ce, and maintenanceMust exhibit competence in at least one of the following analytics/science fields, and in one of the following computing languages:Statistics (2 or more areas):Generalized linear modelsNonparametric regressionBayesian statisticsTime series (State space models, ARIMA, ï¿½)Mixture modelsStructural equation modelsOptimization (at least one):Mixed-integerNon-linearStochasticStochastic Models and Discrete-Event SimulationDecision Analysis or Multiple Criteria Decision MakingEconometrics (2 or more areas):Panel dataLimited dependent variablesGeneralized method of momentsSimultaneous equations modelsInstrumental variablesMachine learning (2 or more areas):CARTRandom forestsNeural networksBoostingSupport vector machinesGraphical modelsClusteringReinforcement learningComputing & programming languages (at least one):Scientific computing (MATLAB, Julia, etc.)Statistical (SAS, R, etc.)General (Java, Python, C, C++, etc.)How To Stand Out:Proven knowledge of revenue management context, including demand forecasting, resource allocation, and pricingPossess a PhD in Statistics, Operations Research, Industrial Engineering, Mathematics, Machine Learning, Econometrics or related field\n\n			\n\n		','\n\n					Lake Buena Vista, FL 					\n\n				','Decision Science Technical Manager\r'),(5,'https://datajobs.com/Disney-Parks-Resorts/Sr-Pricing-Analyst-Job~10507','\n\n			\n\n				\n\n					Job Description\n\n				\n\n			\n\n			\n\n				\n\n					The Revenue Management and Analytics (RM&A) team supports clients across all corporate segments, including Walt Disney Parks & Resorts. Teams support Parks & Resorts lines of business including Admissions, Lodging, Merchandise and Food & Beverage (F&B) in the core competencies of yield management, revenue planning, forecasting, pricing, promotions and optimization. Candidates should have a natural curiosity to understand the \"why\" behind business performance, take a proactive role in problem-solving, be results oriented, be able to prioritize and be a team player in a collaborative environment.This position will develop and analyze pricing and revenue management strategies to maximize overall profitability in the Food & Beverage, Merchandise, Tours & Recreation, and Events lines of business for Walt Disney Parks & Resorts. This position will also work with key partners including Operations, Finance, Experience Integration, Communications/Public Affairs, and internal RM&A partners to execute and measure implemented tactics.Your Role:Help us growï¿½- Identify revenue and profit growth opportunities, evaluate the financial impact of changes to the business, present pricing & revenue management decisions for a wide variety of products & venues. Provide revenue assumptions and projections for new concepts.Provide strategic and tactical supportï¿½ï¿½ Support the development and valuation of the Long Term Plan and Annual Operating Plan (AOP), as well as support evolving measurement methodologies. Lead and/or assist in development of price changes in areas such as Food & Beverage, Disney Dining Plan, Merchandise, Tours & Recreation, etc).Achieve business goals and objectivesï¿½- Develop and maintain reporting on an ad-hoc and recurring basis, build and deliver PowerPoint presentations to partners and clients at various levels in the organization, monitor industry trends and competitive benchmarks, and assist with project management of key business initiatives.Collaborate with key partnersï¿½- Develop and maintain positive service-oriented relationships with partners and clients.What We\'re Looking For:Proven success collaborating with a range of partners understanding multiple perspectivesStrong written and verbal communication skills to convey data and analysis to partners at all levelsDemonstrated ability to lead teams and manage multiple tasks in a fast-paced environmentDemonstrated ability to meet deadlines, handle multiple priorities, and perform job responsibilities accurately with minimal supervisionStrong sense of responsibility, ownership, and pride in delivering quality results for the Food & Beverage line of businessStrong attention to detail, data accuracy and an inquisitiveness to determine explanations, with an ability to consolidate multiple sources of information/analyses into a cohesive story/recommendationAbility to work in a team environment with a positive demeanor, generating innovative solutions to complex challengesDemonstrated strong analytical skillsAdvanced knowledge and skills in Microsoft Excel (e.g., HLOOKUP, VLOOKUP, Pivot Tables, DSUM, If, Macros)Bachelorï¿½s degree in Business, Finance, Industrial Engineering, Economics, Statistics, Mathematics or related fieldHow To Stand Out:Demonstrated strong leadership skillsThree plus yearsï¿½ experience in a role with data analysisPricing and/or revenue management experienceDemonstrated knowledge of Walt Disney Parks & Resorts operations, business units, and product offeringsFamiliarity with the Disney F&B line of business and its unique F&B products including dining plansFamiliarity with Disney F&B source systems (e.g., Matra POS, F&B Data Warehouse, Cogsworh, D3, etc.)Master\'s degree in Finance, Industrial Engineering, Economics, Statistics or related quantitative fieldï¿½\n\n			\n\n		','\n\n					Lake Buena Vista, FL 					\n\n				','Sr Pricing Analyst\r'),(6,'https://datajobs.com/Disney-ABC-Television-Group/Senior-Data-Scientist-Job~10510','\n\n			\n\n				\n\n					Job Description\n\n				\n\n			\n\n			\n\n				\n\n					Are you interested in changing the future of television? The media industry is undergoing rapid change, and Disney-ABC Television is building new data & analytics capabilities that will enable us to complete in this dynamic new marketplace. A new startup group has launched within Disney-ABC Television with the skills and passion to prepare the way for that future and lead a data revolution. The Consumer Data & Analytics team is responsible for innovating, developing, and evang