nthesize information across businessesInfluence and guide the build of predictive models and algorithms to effectively measure and optimize retail performance, partnering with Data Science teamsObtain and analyze data from multiple sources, extracting insights from disparate data setsAnalyze large, complex data sets representing the behavior of millions of guests to address strategic and operational business questionsDistill and communicate key insights across all levels of DCPI\'s organizationDevelop frameworks, models, tools, and processes to institutionalize findingsPrepare and communicate results to internal clients, e.g. marketing, site merchandising, and product at middle to senior level management in the organizationWork closely with internal teams, using data to drive continuous improvement in operations and guest experiencesOversee and manage a teamManage, design, execute continuous and ad-hoc quantitative analysis to solve specific business questions and derive actionable recommendations in an easy to digest mannerConduct sophisticated data analysis and provide actionable recommendations to business problems based on multiple sources of dataBasic Qualifications7+ years of experience in an analysis, market research or consulting role4+ years of experience managing a teamExperience in marketing analytics related to digital retail marketing including email, search, social and displaySeasoned client engagement skills with ability to translate business problems into solution-driven actionsAbility to translate technical findings into actionable recommendations through easy to digest reports and presentationsAbility to work with multiple stakeholders and handle multiple work assignments with high standardsExcellent collaboration skills with the ability to effectively partner across all levels and skill setsAbility to manage multiple projects and provide leadership in a fast-paced environmentExperience using data visualization reporting tools (e.g. Tableau) a plus